  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 30 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1110 mg
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/barbecue-pulled-pork-sandwiches-5a296a30a5ed1967dd007632
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #toaster oven{} or #oven{} to 400 degrees. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}. Peel @carrot{1}, then grate until you have ½ cup grated carrot.

Place grated carrot, scallions, @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}, @sour cream{3%tbsp}, @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp} in a #medium bowl{} and toss to combine (we sent more sour cream and vinegar). Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice @Persian cucumber{1} into thin rounds, then place in a #small bowl{} along with another @sugar{1/2%tsp}, @water{1%tsp}, remaining @white wine vinegar{2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Toss to combine.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add @pulled pork{10%oz}, breaking up meat into pieces with a #wooden spoon{}. Stir in @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tbsp}, @BBQ sauce{4%tbsp}, @ketchup{2%tbsp}, and @water{2%tbsp}. Allow to warm through, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if sauce seems dry.

Meanwhile, split @brioche buns{2} in half and toast in #toaster oven{} or #oven{} until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Fill buns with pork, pickled cucumber, and a little bit of slaw each. Divide between #plates{} and serve with remaining slaw on the side.